## ⚠️ Important Notes

- **Review before execution:** Manually review all obsolete files before moving them
- **External dependencies:** Some files may be used by external tools or scripts
- **Test thoroughly:** Test the application after any cleanup
- **Version control:** Consider committing current state before making changes
- **Archive first:** Files are moved to Archive folder, not deleted permanently
- **Recovery:** You can restore files from Archive if needed

## 🔄 Recovery Commands

If you need to restore files from the archive:

```batch
REM Restore all duplicates
move Archive\Duplicates\* .

REM Restore all obsolete files
move Archive\Obsolete\* .

REM Remove empty archive directories
rmdir Archive\Duplicates
rmdir Archive\Obsolete
rmdir Archive
```
